data.title: NSW take first innings points against Tasmania
data.meta_description: NSW lead Tasmania by 49 runs on day three of the Sheffield Shield clash at Blacktown in Sydney.
data.text:
NSW have taken a 49-run first-innings lead over Tasmania in their Sheffield Shield clash at Blacktown.

The Tigers' tail wagged thanks to some big hitting from Luke Butterworth (49 from 76) and solid support from No.11 Sam Rainbird (16 not out).

Tasmania were eventually bowled out for 239 early on day three, chasing the Blues' total of 288, but the visitors importantly added 44 runs to their overnight score for the final wicket.

Nathan Lyon finally ended the innings for NSW when the Australian spinner had Butterworth caught and bowled in the 98th over.

Blues fast bowler Doug Bollinger was the star for the home side, finishing with figures of 6-62 after a stellar performance on day two.

The left-armer can bring himself back into Test contention with a strong start to the season, given Australia's fast-bowling injury dramas.

The wicket is tipped to deteriorate over the final two days, meaning Tasmania will need to restrict NSW in the second innings to prevent a big chase on the final day.

AAP
